==English==

===Etymology===
From [[supplement]]

===Noun===
''plural''
:(''Geometry'') A pair of angles are supplementary if their respective measures sum to 180 [[degree]]s. The size of one of the angles is called the [[supplement]] of the other. They are typically associated with "angles on a straight line" and [[cyclic quadrilateral]]s, in which opposite angles are supplementary.

